ss=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2011)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|91|artist=The Doobie Brothers|song=Long Train Runnin'|accessdate=July 29, 2013}}\n|}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (2013)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|104|artist=The Doobie Brothers|song=Long Train Runnin'|accessdate=July 29, 2013}}\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|artist=Doobie Brothers|title=Long Train Runnin|award=Silver|relyear=2007|certyear=2019|accessdate=October 11, 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true|noshipments=true|streaming=true}}\n\n==Cover versions==\n===Traks version===\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Long Train Runnin'\n| cover      = Traks - Long Train Runnin'.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = Traks\n| album      = Long Train Runnin'\n| B-side     = Drums Power\n| released   = 1982\n| format     = {{hlist|[[7\" single]]|[[12-inch single|12\" single]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n| length     = 3:30\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Polydor Records|Polydor]]|Savoir-Faire}}\n| writer     = [[Tom Johnston (musician)|Tom Johnston]]\n| producer   = Traks\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Get Ready (The Temptations song)|Get Ready]]\n| next_year  = 1983\n}}\n\nIn 1982, Italian band Traks covered the song. This version charted in France and in Germany, where it peaked at No. 62 and No. 18, respectively.\n\n====Track listing====\n; 7\" single Polydor 2040 365\n#\"Long Train Runnin'\" (short version) \u2013 3:30\n#\"Drums Power\" \u2013 4:27\n\n====Charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1982)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n|France ([[Institut fran\u00e7ais d'opinion publique|IFOP]])<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.infodisc.fr/Bilan_T.php |title= InfoDisc : Tous les Titres par Artiste |publisher= InfoDisc |id=Select \"Traks\" from the artist drop-down menu |accessdate= July 29, 2013 |language= fr |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130920092618/http://infodisc.fr/Bilan_T.php |archivedate= September 20, 2013}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|62\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|18|artist=Traks|song=Long Train Runnin'|songid=75713|accessdate=July 29, 2013|refname=\"GER\"}}\n|}\n\n{{clear}}\n\n===Bananarama version===\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Long Train Running\n| cover      = Bananarama - Long Train Running.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Bananarama]]\n| album      = [[Pop Life (Bananarama album)|Pop Life]]\n| B-side     = Outta Sight\n| released   = 8 April 1991\n| format     = {{hlist|7\" single|10\" picture disc|12\" single|CD single}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]<ref name=\"AM\">{{cite web|first= Stewart |last= Mason |title= Bananarama \u2013 Pop Life |publisher= [[AllMusic]]. [[All Media Network]] |url= http://www.allmusic.com/album/pop-life-mw0000267230 |accessdate= July 29, 2013}}</ref>\n| length     = 3:31\n| label      = [[London Records|London]]\n| writer     = [[Tom Johnston (musician)|Tom Johnston]]\n| producer   = Youth\n| prev_title = [[Preacher Man]]\n| prev_year  = 1990\n| next_title = [[Tripping on Your Love]]\n| next_year  = 1991\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|xVPqlVOeh8s|\"Long Train Running\"}}}}\n}}\n\nBananarama's version appeared on their fifth studio album ''[[Pop Life (Bananarama album)|Pop Life]]'' in 1991<ref name=\"AM\"/> and was released as the album's third single in the UK. The group discovered the song when they were browsing through the record collection of [[Martin Glover|Youth]], producer of the ''Pop Life'' album. They needed one more tune recorded to complete ''Pop Life'' and decided to go with a cover. The song reached No. 10 in Portugal, No. 18 in Ireland and No. 30 in the UK.\n\n====Music video====\nBananarama's [[music video]] features them dressed in black Spanish dresses eating at a decadent feast and performing the song on a large bed in a Spanish castle. Bananarama's then-manager Hilary Shaw appears in the feast scene. The video was directed by [[Nick Egan]].\n\n====Charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (1991)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n|Australia ([[ARIA Charts]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Re: ARIA Charts Peak |url= http://i.imgur.com/9AQCjII.jpg |date= 17 June 2014 |publisher= [[Imgur]] |accessdate= 19 September 2015 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141129020821/http://i.imgur.com/9AQCjII.jpg |archivedate= November 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|179\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|47|artist=Bananarama|song=Long Train Running|accessdate=July 29, 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|45|artist=Bananarama|song=Long Train Running|songid=52009|accessdate=July 29, 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|18|song=Long Train|accessdate=July 29, 2013}}\n|-\n|Italy ([[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|FIMI]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Indice per Interprete: B |publisher= Hit Parade Italia. [[Creative Commons]] |url= http://www.hitparadeitalia.it/indici/per_interprete/ab.htm |accessdate= July 29, 2013 |language= it}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|33\n|-\n|Portugal ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Fonogr\u00e1fica Portuguesa|AFP]])<ref>{{cite magazine|title= Top 10 Sales in Europe |magazine= [[Music & Media]] |volume= 8 |issue= 28 |date= July 13, 1991 |page= 26 |accessdate= March 22, 2018 |url= http://americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/90s/1991/MM-1991-07-13.pdf}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|10\n|-\n{{singlechart|United Kingdom|30|date=1991-04-27|accessdate=July 29, 2013}}\n|}\n\n====Remixes====\n; UK CD single NANCD 24'''\n#\"Long Train Running\" (radio version) \u2013 3:31\n#:<small>Remixed by Mark 'Spike' Stent</small>\n#\"Long Train Running\" (Alma De Noche Mix) \u2013 6:40\n#:<small>Remixed by Mark 'Spike' Stent</small>\n#\"Long Train Running\" (Flamenco CD Mix) \u2013 4:57\n#\"Outta Sight\" \u2013 4:30\n\n; CD promo single'''\n#\